cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper involves the use of deep neural networks for learning eligibility in cancer clinical trials, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of image analysis techniques for identifying cancerous cells also suggests the possibility of computer vision (cs.CV) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) for extracting information from clinical trial eligibility criteria, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
